2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper explores social networks of language users and their role in language evolution. 
3. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses simulation models of diffusion of linguistic innovation. 
4. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also possible as the paper discusses social networks and their impact on language evolution. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses computational models of language change.
